{
    "id": 23616,
    "title": "Opinion Announcement - May 05, 2014",
    "transcript": {
        "title": null,
        "duration": 201.312,
        "sections": [
            {
                "start": 0,
                "stop": 201.312,
                "byte_start": 106496,
                "byte_stop": 911694,
                "turns": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "stop": 7.39,
                        "byte_start": 106496,
                        "byte_stop": 136067,
                        "speaker": null,
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 7.39,
                                "byte_start": 106496,
                                "byte_stop": 136067,
                                "text": "Justice Breyer has our opinion this morning in case 12-9012, Robers versus United States."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 7.39,
                        "stop": 201.312,
                        "byte_start": 136067,
                        "byte_stop": 911694,
                        "speaker": null,
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 7.39,
                                "stop": 15.285,
                                "byte_start": 136067,
                                "byte_stop": 167727,
                                "text": "This case requires us to interpret rather technical statutory provision that concerns restitution."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 15.285,
                                "stop": 21.729,
                                "byte_start": 167727,
                                "byte_stop": 193432,
                                "text": "The restitution of convicted criminal offender must provide to a victim of a property crime."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 21.729,
                                "stop": 29.973,
                                "byte_start": 193432,
                                "byte_stop": 226450,
                                "text": "Now, the petitioner was involved in fraudulently obtaining bank loans amounting to about $470,000."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 29.973,
                                "stop": 40.134,
                                "byte_start": 226450,
                                "byte_stop": 267097,
                                "text": "When he didn\u0027t pay his mortgage, the bank took title to two houses that were collateral for the loans and then the banks later sold the houses."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 40.134,
                                "stop": 56.428,
                                "byte_start": 267097,
                                "byte_stop": 332298,
                                "text": "The real estate market was falling at that time and they sold them for about $280,000 so the petitioner says, \u201cWhen you calculate my restitution you should subtract from the $470,000.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 56.428,
                                "stop": 81.62,
                                "byte_start": 332298,
                                "byte_stop": 433027,
                                "text": "Not the $280,000 that the bank has got back from the sale, but a larger amount than that and then the amount that represented the higher value that the houses had had when the banks first took title to them because remember the real estate market was falling and that\u0027s the amount he wanted subtracted, not the amount that the bank has got back when they sold the houses."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 81.62,
                                "stop": 115.118,
                                "byte_start": 433027,
                                "byte_stop": 566983,
                                "text": "Now, in support of this contention, the petitioner points through a statutory provision that says that when return of the property lost by a victim is impossible or inadequate, the offender must pay the victim \u201can amount equal to\u201d the value of the property which we\u0027ll recall was $470,000, less the value as of the date the property is returned of any part of the property that is returned."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 115.118,
                                "stop": 126.242,
                                "byte_start": 566983,
                                "byte_stop": 611495,
                                "text": "So he says in effect that part of the property taken was returned when the banks took title to the houses and therefore that that property has to be valued as of the date he returned it."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 126.242,
                                "stop": 130.715,
                                "byte_start": 611495,
                                "byte_stop": 629363,
                                "text": "Well, it\u0027s all in writing in case you have trouble following that 2:09."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 130.715,
                                "stop": 139.961,
                                "byte_start": 629363,
                                "byte_stop": 666352,
                                "text": "And the problem for the petitioner is that the statute talks about the property he took and his return of that property."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 139.961,
                                "stop": 143.045,
                                "byte_start": 666352,
                                "byte_stop": 678682,
                                "text": "Here, he did not take the houses."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 143.045,
                                "stop": 161.045,
                                "byte_start": 678682,
                                "byte_stop": 750780,
                                "text": "He took the money and since he took the money that the bank\u0027s loan to him and that property was not returned at all until the money from the houses was obtained by the bank then that\u0027s the money you have to subtract."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 161.045,
                                "stop": 163.705,
                                "byte_start": 750780,
                                "byte_stop": 761334,
                                "text": "That is what the statute says."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 163.705,
                                "stop": 164.875,
                                "byte_start": 761334,
                                "byte_stop": 766036,
                                "text": "You\u0027ve read in this way."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 164.875,
                                "stop": 166.489,
                                "byte_start": 766036,
                                "byte_stop": 772514,
                                "text": "It\u0027s sensible."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 166.489,
                                "stop": 179.957,
                                "byte_start": 772514,
                                "byte_stop": 826326,
                                "text": "It\u0027s easier to administer and there are other provisions of the statute which will give the courts adequate authority to make certain that this reading does not produce double counting or any other form of unfairness."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 179.957,
                                "stop": 183.113,
                                "byte_start": 826326,
                                "byte_stop": 838969,
                                "text": "We explained this in more in our opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 183.113,
                                "stop": 193.363,
                                "byte_start": 838969,
                                "byte_stop": 880034,
                                "text": "The Seventh Circuit concluded that the relevant statutory provision refers to the money taken not for the collateral received and we affirm its determination."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 193.363,
                                "stop": 195.484,
                                "byte_start": 880034,
                                "byte_stop": 888498,
                                "text": "Our decision is unanimous."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 195.484,
                                "stop": 201.312,
                                "byte_start": 888498,
                                "byte_stop": 911694,
                                "text": "Justice Sotomayor has filed a concurring opinion in which she is joined by Justice Ginsburg."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
